WORKS!!

1 - DL Torrent
2 - Mount DVD disk 1 with Daemon tools.  Installer progress bar doesn't show up for some reason, so just be patient and it will eventually ask for disk 2.
3.  Once installed start the program and it will ask for activation.  Click cancel.
4. in the SP1_crack folder click and run fsx_sp1_ENU and let it finish
5. dont start the program yet
6. go to http://www.gameburnworld.com/gp/gamefixes/flightsimulatorx.shtml and click on the second link for SP1.  Downlaod the rar file.  You will get three .dll files  The ones that come with the torrent don't work.  So use these
7.  Go to the main FSX director (for me its programs/microsoft games/Microsoft Flight simulator X)
8.  CREATE a new folder and cut and past the original three dll files into that folder to save them
9. take the three dll files from the site i said to download and past it in that folder (you can just copy and paste and overwrite, buts its safe to create a backup)
10.  That should be it.  Click on the game and it should run.

Ok. I got this thig to work after a FEW days of multiple attemps at installing it.    What I did after downloading was, unpacked both DVD's with WinRar. I then copied the files from DVD 2 and placed those files in DVD 1. I did not over write any files. It will ask you if you want to replace the files while you are moving them into DVD 1. Select NO. Then I ran the installation. It installed. After Installation is done it will try to run the game. Shut it down. Un pack the crack file from DVD 2. WinRar'd the crack file. Then copy/pasted into the installed Flight Simulator folder. Mine was C:\Microsoft Games\Flight Simulator. Then I ran the game. It worked fine. No Broblems at all.

Thanks for the torrent.

Ok i have it.

1.) Mount DVD 1 to a drive using powerISO or UltraISO (like me)

2.) Go to my computer and double-click the drive that you mounted DVD 1 to, the installation will start

3.) When it asks you to insert Disk 2 do not pannic just open DVD 2 with powerISO or UltraISO and mount that to the same drive as DVD 1 

Now click "OK" on the dialog box that asks you for disc 2 and you should be fine 

DO not worry if you think overwriting the mounted drive with DVD 1 will erase all the files...they wont because you have reached the end of disc 1 installation process so them files are already installed on you Hard Drive in C:/Program files/Microsoft Games/Flight Simulator X

Now go ahead and install Service Pack 1!!!
Your ready to go enjoy your flights

For your own safety Put  The full torrent onto a disc incase your system fails or you have to reboot your whole system

Hope this Helps you all that are stuck and happy flying :)
